    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-06-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-06-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="266" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d266">
                <head>No. 263.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CEDL1" type="from">De Long</persName> to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HF1" type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States
                                    Legation, Yokohama, Japan</hi>
                        </placeName>,<lb/>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-06-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi>
                                21, 1873</date>. (Received July 22.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 433.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that I have
                        just received a note from Senor Aurilio Garcia y Garcia, the Peruvian envoy,
                        which reads as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation del Peru,
                                    Yedo</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 20, 1873.</p>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Friend</hi>: After a very long
                                discussion with the minister for foreign affairs, Mr. Woogem, which
                                I asked for in view of his answer to my dispatch on the Maria <pb facs="0703" n="617" xml:id="pg_617"/> Luz case, we agreed
                                yesterday and have signed a protocol referring that case to the
                                arbitration of the chief of a friendly state. The difference between
                                Peru and Japan has thus ended.</p>
                        <p>The only thing to be done now is to select the arbitrator and submit
                                the case to him.</p>
                        <p>Convinced that this news will be gratifying to you,</p>
                        <p>I am, yours very sincerely,</p>
                        <p rend="right">A. G. <hi rend="smallcaps">y</hi> GARCIA.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>His Excellency <persName corresp="#p_CEDL1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">C. E. De
                                Long</hi>
                    </persName>, &amp;c.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CEDL1">C. E. DE LONG</persName>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
